@subsection Testing for Equality and Performing Unification 

Variables of type @code{ciao_term} cannot be tested directly for equality: they are (currently) implemented as a sort of pointers which may be aliased (two different pointers may refer to the same object). The interface provides helper functions for testing term equality and to perform unification of terms. 


@itemize @bullet{} 
@item @code{ciao_bool ciao_unify(ciao_term x, ciao_term y);} 

Performs the unification of the terms @code{x} and @code{y}, and returns true if the unification was successful. This is equivalent to calling the (infix) Prolog predicate @code{=/2}. The bindings are trailed and undone on backtracking. 


@item @code{ciao_bool ciao_equal(ciao_term x, ciao_term y);} 

Performs equality testing of terms, and returns true if the test was successful. This is equivalent to calling the (infix) Prolog predicate @code{==/2}. Equality testing does not modify the terms compared. 


@end itemize  
 

