@subsection Raising Exceptions 

The following functions offers a way of throwing 
@glindex exceptions
exceptions from C that can be caught in Prolog with @code{catch/3}. The term that reaches Prolog is exactly the same which was thrown by C. The execution flow is broken at the point where @code{ciao_raise_exception()} is executed, and it returns to Prolog. 


@itemize @bullet{} 


@item @code{void ciao_raise_exception(ciao_term ball);} 

Raises an exception an throws the term @code{ball}. 


@end itemize  
 

