This package allows to write and evaluate constraint programming expressions over finite domains in a Ciao program. It is based upon the indexicals concept. 

The syntax of this constraint system is described below: 


@itemize @bullet{} 


@item @emph{c ::= X in r} (@emph{r} is the range of variable @emph{X}). 
@item @emph{c ::= E1 .=. E2} (eventual value of expression @emph{E1} equals @emph{E2}) 
@item @emph{c ::= E1 .<>. E2} (@emph{E1} differs from @emph{E2}) 
@item @emph{c ::= E1 .<. E2} (@emph{E1} is lower than @emph{E2}) 
@item @emph{c ::= E1 .>. E2} (@emph{E1} is greater than @emph{E2}) 
@item @emph{c ::= E1 .=<. E2} (@emph{E1} is lower or equal than @emph{E2}) 
@item @emph{c ::= E1 .>=. E2} (@emph{E1} is greater or equal than @emph{E2}) 


@item @emph{r ::= r1} (one interval range). 
@item @emph{r ::= r1 .&. r} (multi interval range). 
@item @emph{r1 ::= t..t} (interval range). 
@item @emph{r1 ::= dom(X)} (indexical domain, e.g., @emph{X in dom(Y)} means @emph{"X in the domain of Y"}). 
@item @emph{t::= n} (integer). 
@item @emph{t::= min(X)} (indexical min). 
@item @emph{t::= max(X)} (indexical max). 
@end itemize  


